WEBVTT

00:00.887 --> 00:03.891
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

00:18.539 --> 00:21.342
(HAUNTING MUSIC)

00:36.616 --> 00:41.616
Subtitles by explosiveskull

01:19.332 --> 01:21.666
(WATER SPLASHING)

01:21.668 --> 01:24.504
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:50.697 --> 01:53.033
(SNORING)

01:56.969 --> 01:59.303
(REEL CLICKING)

01:59.305 --> 02:02.108
(BIRD SQUAWKING)

02:05.145 --> 02:06.877
Do you see that, captain?

02:06.879 --> 02:08.048
Yeah.

02:09.681 --> 02:10.815
I see him.

02:10.817 --> 02:12.816
(BIRD SQUAWKING)

02:12.818 --> 02:14.888
Alright, what do you think man?

02:15.622 --> 02:17.291
Do you think the beast is close?

02:19.826 --> 02:22.727
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

02:22.729 --> 02:23.793
What do you say, Duke?

02:23.795 --> 02:25.863
He's done there somewhere.

02:25.865 --> 02:28.302
Making up his damn mind.

02:30.069 --> 02:31.803
(BOAT CREAKING)

02:31.805 --> 02:32.870
(REEL CLICKING)

02:32.872 --> 02:34.241
(WATER SPLASHING)

02:34.907 --> 02:40.146
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)
(LAUGHING)

02:43.883 --> 02:45.551
Woohoo, yeah boy!

02:46.919 --> 02:48.720
- Holy fuck.
- Alright.

02:48.722 --> 02:50.356
- Duke get the fight jacket.
- Huh!

02:51.191 --> 02:52.590
Dill, what are you doing?

02:52.592 --> 02:54.024
The hook is set.

02:54.026 --> 02:56.526
You're going to hand over the
rod to the paying customer.

02:56.528 --> 02:58.665
No, Duke, it's him.

02:59.900 --> 03:02.500
How can you possibly
know it's the same fish?

03:02.502 --> 03:03.270
I can feel it.

03:04.204 --> 03:05.836
You take the wheel
and hold it steady.

03:05.838 --> 03:06.937
Okay, sir.

03:06.939 --> 03:08.673
Can I take over the
rod now, please?

03:08.675 --> 03:10.108
Here we go baby.

03:10.110 --> 03:11.942
Sir, we paid you
700 bucks for this.

03:11.944 --> 03:13.612
Dill, he's right, his hook.

03:13.614 --> 03:16.050
Get out of the chair and
give the man the rod.

03:16.550 --> 03:17.749
(REEL CLICKING)

03:17.751 --> 03:19.116
(WATER BUBBLING)

03:19.118 --> 03:20.285
Hey, that's my
brother's fish there.

03:20.287 --> 03:21.722
Get off the fucking chair.

03:23.789 --> 03:24.788
You get the in hole.

03:24.790 --> 03:25.790
Oh, man.

03:25.792 --> 03:27.459
You sit down and
shut the fuck up.

03:27.461 --> 03:28.091
The both of you.

03:28.093 --> 03:28.959
Son of a bitch.

03:28.961 --> 03:30.627
We paid you 700 bucks and gas.

03:30.629 --> 03:32.198
- Okay, okay.
- Now!

03:33.199 --> 03:35.469
- Okay, okay.
- Get the fuck out of here.

03:37.302 --> 03:38.970
It looks like this
is a trophy fish guys.

03:38.972 --> 03:41.207
Go get some beers,
enjoy the show, yeah?

03:43.575 --> 03:44.976
Duke, take the wheel.

03:44.978 --> 03:46.977
He's headed to open water.

03:46.979 --> 03:48.046
Follow him.

03:48.048 --> 03:51.652
Damn you, oh, here we go kid.

03:52.385 --> 03:54.587
(GROANING)

04:03.597 --> 04:06.464
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

04:06.466 --> 04:08.135
(REEL CLICKING)

04:10.469 --> 04:12.338
(COUGHING)

04:14.507 --> 04:15.509
Fuck.

04:25.985 --> 04:28.688
(REEL RATTLING)

04:29.855 --> 04:32.589
(GRUNTING)

04:32.591 --> 04:35.596
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

04:39.031 --> 04:42.666
(HAUNTING MUSIC)

04:42.668 --> 04:43.669
We got it.

04:44.704 --> 04:45.706
Duke?

04:52.678 --> 04:53.379
Take the leader.

04:53.779 --> 04:54.880
He's spent.

04:54.882 --> 04:56.716
No, he still has
spunk in him Dill.

04:57.718 --> 05:00.554
No, no, he's
dead in the water.

05:02.788 --> 05:03.790
Yeah.

05:11.564 --> 05:12.697
You got him?

05:12.699 --> 05:13.734
Bring him up.

05:15.235 --> 05:18.237
No, no, no, he's
done, bring him up.

05:19.838 --> 05:20.904
There he is.

05:20.906 --> 05:21.738
(GRUNTING)

05:21.740 --> 05:22.740
Easy.

05:22.742 --> 05:24.041
That's right.

05:24.043 --> 05:25.512
Come on, Duke.

05:25.978 --> 05:27.144
Here we go.

05:27.146 --> 05:28.579
Nice and steady.

05:28.581 --> 05:31.514
(GRUNTING)

05:31.516 --> 05:32.985
We got him this time.

05:34.387 --> 05:38.591
(LINE WHOOSHING)
No, no, no, no!

05:41.495 --> 05:42.760
(GROANING)

05:42.762 --> 05:45.697
You think we're gonna pay
you a fucking single dollar

05:45.699 --> 05:47.065
for this fiasco,

05:47.067 --> 05:47.834
(CAN TAB CLICKING)

05:48.767 --> 05:50.736
you're out of your fucking mind.

05:54.240 --> 05:59.245
(GROANING)
(TENSE MUSIC)

06:56.836 --> 06:59.303
Lieutenant Gonzales said
without a paper contract

06:59.305 --> 07:00.937
there's nothing that we can do.

07:00.939 --> 07:02.807
So, the gringos don't pay,

07:02.809 --> 07:04.074
no kingfish to sell to Lionel

07:04.076 --> 07:06.610
because you spent
all day on tuna.

07:06.612 --> 07:07.613
I'll pay you.

07:09.014 --> 07:10.281
Okay?

07:10.283 --> 07:12.283
Yeah, how?

07:12.285 --> 07:14.618
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

07:14.620 --> 07:16.353
(WOMAN MOANING)

07:16.355 --> 07:20.460
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

07:32.372 --> 07:33.706
Mr. Baker Dill,

07:34.973 --> 07:38.644
I am increasingly fond
of the way you say hello.

07:42.182 --> 07:45.886
(MUFFLED SPEAKING ON RADIO)

07:47.387 --> 07:50.624
Jack said he heard two
fat guys in the rope,

07:51.357 --> 07:53.227
said you pulled a knife on them.

07:57.562 --> 07:58.562
You ever thought about taking

07:58.564 --> 08:00.731
a course in customer relations?

08:00.733 --> 08:02.903
(GROANING)

08:04.336 --> 08:05.469
And by the way,

08:05.471 --> 08:07.404
have you seen my damn cat?

08:07.406 --> 08:08.673
He was up at Joe's.

08:08.675 --> 08:10.841
He gone jealous
feeding him sprites.

08:10.843 --> 08:12.978
You made it all the
way up to the countering

08:12.980 --> 08:15.482
before you decided to
turn around and see me.

08:16.048 --> 08:17.584
Why'd you come Dill?

08:18.752 --> 08:20.387
Why do you think?

08:21.187 --> 08:22.353
Well, it's just
I heard you went

08:22.355 --> 08:24.221
to the Mercantile
Bank this morning.

08:24.223 --> 08:25.156
Who'd you get?

08:25.158 --> 08:27.757
Carter, asshole.

08:27.759 --> 08:28.758
How'd you do?

08:28.760 --> 08:31.329
Oh, Connie seems you
know damn well how I did.

08:31.331 --> 08:33.565
Around here everybody
knows everything.

08:33.567 --> 08:36.099
Well I heard the bank
refused to extend your loan.

08:36.101 --> 08:38.605
So now you can't
even afford gas.

08:40.407 --> 08:41.605
I'm just a little
hurt that you got

08:41.607 --> 08:43.707
all the way as far
as Joe's place

08:43.710 --> 08:46.713
before you decided
I'm the last resort.

08:47.746 --> 08:48.447
Baker Dill.

08:49.414 --> 08:50.416
You're no more than a hooker.

08:51.350 --> 08:52.949
Hooker who can't afford hooks.

08:52.951 --> 08:54.352
(KEYS JANGLING)

08:54.354 --> 08:56.286
(TENSE MUSIC)

08:56.288 --> 08:57.390
How's your son?

08:58.124 --> 09:00.090
Still pumping gas in Miami.

09:00.092 --> 09:01.092
Why?

09:01.094 --> 09:03.127
Well he was good
around a boat.

09:03.129 --> 09:04.362
If he wants to quit pumping gas,

09:04.364 --> 09:05.432
I'd take him on.

09:06.065 --> 09:07.467
What's wrong with Duke?

09:08.868 --> 09:11.305
I don't know, he's
gone a little crazy.

09:12.371 --> 09:13.572
Him or you?

09:15.975 --> 09:18.577
You know, Duke's got
a grandkid in college.

09:19.979 --> 09:21.478
He needs work that pays.

09:21.480 --> 09:24.547
(MUFFLED SPEAKING ON RADIO)

09:24.549 --> 09:26.952
How dare old Joe feed my cat?

09:28.721 --> 09:31.122
I like my cats to depend on me.

09:31.124 --> 09:33.156
(LIGHT MUSIC)

09:33.158 --> 09:34.561
My sweet kitty.

09:35.494 --> 09:39.499
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

09:52.177 --> 09:54.681
(WHISTLING)

10:07.994 --> 10:08.995
Hey Dill.

10:11.029 --> 10:12.031
One for old Wes.

10:20.139 --> 10:21.975
There you go, Wes.

10:23.009 --> 10:24.543
Heard you had him
on again, Dill.

10:25.610 --> 10:28.878
Wes wonders if it isn't
the same big old tuna

10:28.880 --> 10:30.384
that broke his heart.

10:34.888 --> 10:37.557
You've hooked him five
times since New Year, right?

10:37.889 --> 10:38.891
Four.

10:40.125 --> 10:41.394
Why don't you give him a name?

10:42.193 --> 10:44.463
Me and the boys were saying
you should give him a name.

10:45.163 --> 10:46.699
I already gave him a name.

10:49.402 --> 10:52.004
(TENSE MUSIC)

10:55.908 --> 10:57.644
His name is Justice.

10:59.544 --> 11:01.512
(LIGHT ACOUSTIC MUSIC)

11:01.514 --> 11:05.685
(MURMURING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

11:10.157 --> 11:12.826
(BELL RINGING)

11:35.081 --> 11:37.113
Tomorrow morning, 5:30.

11:37.115 --> 11:38.916
You got money for gas?

11:38.918 --> 11:40.787
If I didn't,
where would we go?

11:41.453 --> 11:43.621
So how many have we got?

11:43.623 --> 11:46.190
Dill, how many paying customers
we taking out tomorrow?

11:46.192 --> 11:47.626
None, Duke.

11:48.961 --> 11:49.861
Just you and me.

11:49.863 --> 11:51.362
We can afford to waste gas?

11:51.364 --> 11:53.033
That was him today.

11:55.967 --> 11:57.203
It was him.

11:58.471 --> 11:59.570
(TENSE MUSIC)

11:59.572 --> 12:02.640
Dear Lord, can't
you put that man

12:02.642 --> 12:05.243
and that damn fish together?

12:05.245 --> 12:08.048
(WAVES CRASHING)

12:13.119 --> 12:15.986
RADIO ANNOUNCER: Tomorrow's
low tide at number 25,

12:15.988 --> 12:17.722
high tide 2100.

12:17.724 --> 12:20.994
Set fair for a
beautiful, lovely day.

12:22.261 --> 12:24.497
(WIND WHISTLING)

12:25.331 --> 12:27.167
(CAT MEOWS)

12:28.500 --> 12:30.169
Come here, kitty cat.

12:31.004 --> 12:32.172
Mama wants you home.

12:32.839 --> 12:35.242
(CAT MEOWING)

12:45.183 --> 12:46.519
(CORK POPS)

12:54.326 --> 12:55.528
Sorry kid.

13:01.267 --> 13:02.869
Could have sworn he was spent.

13:04.136 --> 13:05.838
Could feel it in my hands.

13:07.706 --> 13:10.644
(PENSIVE MUSIC)

13:23.389 --> 13:25.825
(LAUGHING)

13:43.909 --> 13:44.809
(SPLASHING)

13:44.811 --> 13:45.642
- That fucking motherfucker!
- Help!

13:45.644 --> 13:47.377
(ALARM CLOCK RINGING)

13:47.379 --> 13:50.015
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

13:55.721 --> 13:57.088
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

13:57.090 --> 13:58.722
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
Good morning,

13:58.724 --> 14:02.593
this is Plymouth Radio,
broadcasting to Plymouth Island

14:02.595 --> 14:04.364
and the ocean all around.

14:05.597 --> 14:07.765
It's another beautiful
morning here on Plymouth,

14:07.767 --> 14:10.667
most beautiful island in
this damn, dirty world.

14:10.669 --> 14:13.771
Temperature, mid 80s,
humidity, just perfect,

14:13.773 --> 14:16.541
and the air smells
of sweet sugar cane.

14:16.543 --> 14:18.945
A perfect day to go out
there on the ocean

14:19.778 --> 14:21.880
and catch that damn fish.

14:22.782 --> 14:25.248
("MAMA TOLD PAPA"
BY CLIFTON CHENIER)

14:25.250 --> 14:26.849
♪ Well Papa told Mama ♪

14:26.851 --> 14:27.785
♪ Well Mama told Papa ♪

14:27.787 --> 14:28.785
♪ Last night she heard ♪

14:28.787 --> 14:30.253
♪ Last night she heard ♪

14:30.255 --> 14:31.454
♪ Yeah Papa told Mama ♪

14:31.456 --> 14:32.690
♪ Oh Papa told Mama ♪

14:32.692 --> 14:37.263
♪ Who didn't believe a word ♪

14:38.197 --> 14:39.963
♪ I wanna grab you oh ♪

14:39.965 --> 14:41.632
♪ Til the break of day ♪

14:41.634 --> 14:43.467
♪ Until the break
of day, oh yeah ♪

14:43.469 --> 14:44.734
That was Mama Told Papa.

14:44.736 --> 14:47.307
What did Mama tell Papa?

14:48.307 --> 14:51.144
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

14:53.546 --> 14:54.978
Alright, Kali.

14:54.980 --> 14:56.980
Just give me the damn fish, huh?

14:56.982 --> 14:58.250
(SMASHES)

15:17.336 --> 15:18.672
(REEL CLICKING)

15:35.620 --> 15:36.822
Duke?

15:40.259 --> 15:41.260
Reel him in.

15:43.328 --> 15:45.264
We're done for the day.

15:59.043 --> 16:00.477
I'll take the bait
to Lionel and at least

16:00.479 --> 16:01.448
get something for it.

16:02.548 --> 16:05.482
No Duke, we don't
deal fucking bait.

16:05.484 --> 16:08.050
(SPLASHES)

16:08.052 --> 16:10.020
You know what, maybe
it's about fucking luck.

16:10.022 --> 16:10.954
Huh?

16:10.956 --> 16:12.792
Maybe you're bringing
me bad luck, Duke.

16:14.460 --> 16:17.163
Ever since your wife died
we haven't caught jack shit.

16:20.566 --> 16:22.802
(BANGS)

16:25.337 --> 16:25.871
That's right.

16:26.806 --> 16:29.475
Find yourself a
commercial boat, huh?

16:36.749 --> 16:37.984
Alright kid.

16:40.419 --> 16:41.420
Just you and me now.

16:44.890 --> 16:47.760
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

16:55.433 --> 16:57.269
Let me get a swizzle.

16:58.437 --> 17:00.170
You know Dill there's
an Indian woman out by

17:00.172 --> 17:02.773
Mason's boatyard who says
you can adjust people's luck.

17:02.775 --> 17:04.940
She got that Argentinian
couple a baby.

17:04.942 --> 17:06.876
I don't need a baby, Jack.

17:06.877 --> 17:07.777
You need something, man.

17:07.779 --> 17:09.613
Yeah, I need a drink.

17:09.615 --> 17:11.951
Thought we established that.

17:12.851 --> 17:14.550
Percentages are not science.

17:14.553 --> 17:17.257
Can't tell the future from
the past, you need instinct.

17:18.057 --> 17:19.792
I hear you just lost that.

17:22.961 --> 17:25.131
Duke was in here about
half an hour ago.

17:26.932 --> 17:29.235
Says he's available for
the morning shift.

17:30.602 --> 17:32.635
Dr. Bob was in here drinking.

17:32.637 --> 17:34.238
Said he heard about the knife.

17:34.240 --> 17:35.940
Said maybe you should
go and see him,

17:35.942 --> 17:37.807
talk to him about
your state of mind.

17:37.809 --> 17:40.544
Was that before or
after his third tequila?

17:40.546 --> 17:42.144
Now you and I joke about that

17:42.146 --> 17:44.149
but some of the
guys are concerned.

17:45.416 --> 17:47.984
There's money in fishing
swordfish at night.

17:47.986 --> 17:50.153
No asshole tourists on board.

17:50.155 --> 17:52.157
Lionel pays for grunts
and flat fish too.

17:53.425 --> 17:54.824
I fish tuna.

17:54.826 --> 17:56.826
- (CLAPPING)
- You fish for one tuna, man,

17:56.828 --> 17:59.398
and that's a tuna that's
only in your head.

17:59.965 --> 18:02.467
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

18:08.273 --> 18:09.508
I'll get that.

18:18.851 --> 18:20.253
Good to see you, John.

18:22.855 --> 18:24.689
I'll have a sparkling water too.

18:24.691 --> 18:26.192
Ice and lemon?

18:26.592 --> 18:27.594
Why not?

18:30.430 --> 18:31.431
So.

18:32.664 --> 18:33.866
What do you say?

18:36.368 --> 18:38.701
Say I'm not called
John anymore.

18:38.703 --> 18:40.371
Fate's funny, huh?

18:40.373 --> 18:41.971
Okay Karen.

18:41.973 --> 18:44.307
I don't believe in coincidence.

18:44.309 --> 18:45.510
Neither do I.

18:49.681 --> 18:51.217
Welcome to Plymouth, ma'am.

18:52.116 --> 18:53.185
Do you have a place here?

18:53.819 --> 18:54.820
Maybe we can go to dinner?

18:55.788 --> 18:57.623
Only places that are
open you're in it.

18:58.557 --> 19:01.225
I'd like to talk to
you someplace private.

19:01.227 --> 19:02.959
I'd like to know what
the fuck you're doing

19:02.961 --> 19:04.694
out here on the edge of nowhere.

19:04.696 --> 19:06.565
I came to tell
you you were right

19:07.967 --> 19:09.535
and I was wrong.

19:13.705 --> 19:16.174
(CHUCKLING)

19:18.376 --> 19:19.378
Fuck.

19:21.913 --> 19:23.682
I hear you have a boat.

19:28.653 --> 19:29.521
You own this boat?

19:30.088 --> 19:32.258
Well, me and the
bank, we take turns.

19:34.859 --> 19:37.494
This is about as
private as it gets.

19:37.496 --> 19:39.198
How did you find me
and what do you want?

19:40.398 --> 19:41.832
Back in the real world
they got this thing

19:41.834 --> 19:44.235
called Facebook, you
ever heard of it?

19:44.237 --> 19:45.038
Nope.

19:45.938 --> 19:47.437
Well, when I decided
to track you down

19:47.439 --> 19:49.342
I reached out to some
of the guys from school.

19:50.276 --> 19:52.010
You remember Dodie,
the relentless one?

19:53.112 --> 19:55.444
Well he put together a class
reunion a couple years ago,

19:55.446 --> 19:58.216
only two who didn't
show were you and me.

19:59.117 --> 20:00.619
Nobody knew where you were.

20:02.288 --> 20:06.025
Everybody knew about
Iraq and the medals.

20:08.227 --> 20:10.559
So little Greg had gone
fishing on this boat

20:10.561 --> 20:14.030
on some island in the middle
of nowhere and he had caught

20:14.032 --> 20:17.468
a fish and had his photo
taken with it and he said

20:17.470 --> 20:19.603
that there was this
guy in the shot

20:19.605 --> 20:21.203
who looked just like John Mason.

20:21.205 --> 20:26.311
Only he said the guy was
calling himself Baker Dill.

20:27.145 --> 20:28.446
Was it a big fish?

20:28.448 --> 20:29.813
Excuse me?

20:29.815 --> 20:32.418
He had his photo taken, it
must have been a big fish.

20:34.286 --> 20:36.086
So we tracked down the photo.

20:36.088 --> 20:38.154
Couldn't tell if it was you
standing there or not but

20:38.156 --> 20:39.924
the name gave it
away, Baker Dill.

20:40.726 --> 20:43.626
Dillon Baker was the only
teacher you respected at Morgan.

20:43.628 --> 20:45.261
He taught math, right?

20:45.263 --> 20:48.567
You still haven't
told me what you want.

20:49.935 --> 20:51.634
Figured if you were
using an assumed name

20:51.636 --> 20:52.835
you were on the run.

20:52.837 --> 20:54.304
I'm just waiting on
some things back home

20:54.306 --> 20:56.273
to lose their significance.

20:56.275 --> 20:59.610
I thought you being outside
the law would be okay.

20:59.612 --> 21:01.014
In fact it would be good.

21:03.015 --> 21:04.684
'Cause like I say,

21:06.184 --> 21:09.454
you were right and I was wrong.

21:09.855 --> 21:11.124
About Frank.

21:12.357 --> 21:13.459
(TENSE MUSIC)

21:13.692 --> 21:19.031
He got richer and bigger
and drunker and angrier.

21:19.632 --> 21:21.597
Hands turned to fists...

21:21.599 --> 21:22.801
So get a divorce.

21:23.634 --> 21:25.337
Except I guess you can't.

21:25.971 --> 21:27.173
No, I can't.

21:29.641 --> 21:33.209
He's even more connected than
he was, Cubans out of Miami.

21:33.211 --> 21:35.511
I try to leave, he'd
found a hole for me

21:35.513 --> 21:37.847
in one of his
construction sites.

21:37.849 --> 21:39.351
That's the truth.

21:41.787 --> 21:45.220
