how to catch tuna.

45:26.409 --> 45:29.480
Hey, school for you
tomorrow, Captain Dole.

45:29.980 --> 45:31.112
You're the boss.

45:31.114 --> 45:32.082
Fuckin' A I'm the boss.

45:32.717 --> 45:34.816
Gonna wash my hands,
okay, you pay the guy.

45:34.818 --> 45:37.489
Watch his eyes pop out
of his fuckin' head.

45:39.590 --> 45:42.159
(TENSE MUSIC)

45:47.764 --> 45:48.766
So.

45:49.766 --> 45:50.768
Tomorrow.

45:52.603 --> 45:53.668
You pay me another 10,

45:53.670 --> 45:55.271
we do the same thing
again tomorrow.

45:55.273 --> 45:57.173
- John.
- We fish, we come back.

45:57.175 --> 45:58.240
You've spent one day with him.

45:58.242 --> 45:59.508
I have had 10 years.

45:59.510 --> 46:00.845
Karen, you got the money.

46:01.512 --> 46:02.744
Go to Europe, go anywhere,

46:02.746 --> 46:05.414
just keep that fuckin'
animal away from my son.

46:05.416 --> 46:06.849
And have him hunt us?

46:06.851 --> 46:08.150
Him?
Come on.

46:08.152 --> 46:08.851
Honey!

46:08.853 --> 46:10.788
Fuckin' blood everywhere here!

46:11.188 --> 46:12.820
(LAUGHING)

46:12.822 --> 46:14.757
John, the 10 million
is dirty money,

46:14.759 --> 46:17.027
it's in cash, it's yours.

46:21.998 --> 46:22.831
(SIGHS)

46:22.833 --> 46:24.766
Okay John you want the truth?

46:24.768 --> 46:27.170
Your son wants you to
do it, this is his idea.

46:28.206 --> 46:31.175
You're his father, he
needs you to do this.

46:32.710 --> 46:33.878
He wants justice.

46:35.112 --> 46:36.711
Baby, come on, let's
go up to the hotel

46:36.713 --> 46:37.949
and get a cocktail.

46:38.949 --> 46:41.650
Early to bed for you
boys, school tomorrow.

46:41.652 --> 46:44.621
Tuna, T-U-N-A.

46:49.826 --> 46:51.728
Talk to me about temptation.

46:54.032 --> 46:56.834
(WAVES CRASHING)

47:07.577 --> 47:09.179
I know you, Dill.

47:10.847 --> 47:13.585
The way you looked at him,
the way you looked at her.

47:14.485 --> 47:16.083
You knew her before.

47:16.085 --> 47:16.751
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

47:16.753 --> 47:19.690
Yeah, more than that.

47:20.157 --> 47:21.326
What happened?

47:23.693 --> 47:25.596
I went away to war.

47:27.030 --> 47:28.666
War fucked me up.

47:31.768 --> 47:33.937
Came back and she was with him.

47:37.742 --> 47:39.911
Except I didn't really
ever come back.

47:44.681 --> 47:46.384
What about that kid
he was talking about?

47:47.518 --> 47:49.717
Yeah Duke, you remember
when I hired you

47:49.719 --> 47:52.521
how many rules about
discussing the past?

47:52.523 --> 47:54.356
I'm not talking
about the past.

47:54.358 --> 47:56.391
I'm talking about
today, on deck.

47:56.393 --> 47:58.559
I've spent so long
on boats with you

47:58.561 --> 47:59.364
I can hear you thinking.

48:00.731 --> 48:02.800
So that kid from previous
fuck up is yours?

48:06.737 --> 48:09.940
And how much did she offer
you to kill her husband?

48:16.646 --> 48:19.083
(CHUCKLING)

48:20.251 --> 48:22.120
(TENSE MUSIC)

48:22.952 --> 48:24.719
Who's crazy now, huh?

48:24.721 --> 48:27.490
Dill, even if that
bastard deserves it,

48:27.990 --> 48:30.561
even if Lieutenant Gonzales
won't raise a finger,

48:30.994 --> 48:33.295
there's right and
wrong, heaven and hell.

48:33.297 --> 48:35.998
You know Duke you
made two grand in a day.

48:36.000 --> 48:39.233
I think it's best you go find
someplace safe to put it.

48:39.235 --> 48:40.267
What about tomorrow?

48:40.269 --> 48:41.336
What about tomorrow?

48:41.338 --> 48:42.974
This will blow
over by morning.

48:43.474 --> 48:44.342
You know it.

48:45.242 --> 48:46.608
So, tell me about tomorrow.

48:46.610 --> 48:48.008
Am I hired to come along,

48:48.010 --> 48:49.913
or are you going out
with him alone?

48:50.581 --> 48:51.679
I'll sleep on it.

48:51.681 --> 48:53.183
I doubt you'll sleep.

48:56.853 --> 48:58.288
There is a god, Dill.

48:59.856 --> 49:01.358
And you're a good man.

49:02.659 --> 49:06.196
Catch the fish in your
head, that is the rule.

49:06.931 --> 49:08.932
Do not kill the man.

49:19.143 --> 49:21.878
(PENSIVE MUSIC)

50:00.250 --> 50:03.221
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

50:06.757 --> 50:08.523
FRANK: Can you
fuckin' hear me?

50:08.525 --> 50:10.393
- Get the fuck up!
- Dad!

50:19.769 --> 50:20.834
Huh.

50:20.836 --> 50:22.840
My poor, sweet kitty.

50:49.632 --> 50:50.900
BAKER: What are
you doing here?

50:50.902 --> 50:53.471
He went looking around
the commercial harbour.

50:54.304 --> 50:55.206
John?

50:56.572 --> 50:58.975
All these years I never
stopped thinking about you.

51:00.309 --> 51:01.311
Look.

51:03.713 --> 51:05.949
You put it on my
finger when I was 16.

51:06.751 --> 51:07.950
You remember?

51:07.952 --> 51:10.151
Outside the fix in
the parking lot?

51:10.153 --> 51:11.155
I kept it.

51:11.755 --> 51:12.990
It's the same one.

51:13.456 --> 51:14.655
Brass.

51:14.657 --> 51:16.492
You took it from the
burner on the stove

51:16.494 --> 51:17.825
of your dad's boat.

51:17.827 --> 51:18.992
(PENSIVE MUSIC)

51:18.994 --> 51:21.498
No, that's just some
old ring you found.

51:23.666 --> 51:24.902
No.

51:26.070 --> 51:32.410
You said with this stupid
ring, I thee wed, baby.

51:33.309 --> 51:35.078
I remember it word for word.

51:35.612 --> 51:36.847
And then you left.

51:37.280 --> 51:38.282
I kept it.

51:40.016 --> 51:41.918
I wear it when I'm alone.

51:46.690 --> 51:48.259
You remember that night.

51:48.858 --> 51:50.527
We went to the bridge.

51:51.195 --> 51:52.530
You were fishing.

51:53.597 --> 51:54.966
Eels and jacks.

51:55.965 --> 52:01.605
Then you said I was
finally old enough.

52:02.606 --> 52:05.543
First time for me.

52:07.010 --> 52:08.478
First time ever.

52:09.846 --> 52:09.880
(SIGHS)

52:11.347 --> 52:15.052
If we could go back to
that bridge, that night,

52:15.652 --> 52:16.653
would you go?

52:18.322 --> 52:20.191
What you mean no
war, no fuck up,

52:21.557 --> 52:24.793
no body parts laying around
in the sand in my arms,

52:24.795 --> 52:25.793
my fuckin' hands?

52:25.795 --> 52:26.998
John.

52:29.500 --> 52:31.369
(CRYING)

52:32.235 --> 52:35.239
I loved you even
after you were gone.

52:40.409 --> 52:41.344
Listen up.

52:41.744 --> 52:44.347
Before this gets any
crazier, here's the deal.

52:47.250 --> 52:49.418
I will take him out tomorrow.

52:49.420 --> 52:50.584
He will drink.

52:50.586 --> 52:52.023
He will fall overboard.

52:52.722 --> 52:53.925
The sharks will get the heat

52:54.724 --> 52:56.927
and I will get 10
million in cash.

52:57.661 --> 52:59.594
Afterwards, I will go somewhere,

52:59.596 --> 53:01.331
you will bring my son to me

53:02.264 --> 53:03.701
and then we'll see what happens.

53:04.768 --> 53:07.170
But don't you bullshit
me about love.

53:08.105 --> 53:10.438
I'm doing this for
him, Patrick, my son.

53:10.440 --> 53:13.775
You and me are not
part of the deal.

53:13.777 --> 53:15.209
Okay, okay.

53:15.211 --> 53:17.181
People don't change.

53:17.614 --> 53:20.250
(TENSE MUSIC)

53:21.918 --> 53:24.422
I'm still the
girl at the bridge.

53:51.748 --> 53:54.652
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

54:35.791 --> 54:38.459
We're both destroyed, right?

54:38.461 --> 54:39.927
Both damaged.

54:39.929 --> 54:42.365
Both damaged in
different places.

54:53.610 --> 54:55.713
(MOANING)

55:36.920 --> 55:38.088
That's it.

55:39.722 --> 55:40.724
I beat him.

55:41.425 --> 55:42.426
I win.

55:43.260 --> 55:44.825
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

55:44.827 --> 55:47.163
Make sure you don't get him
there til noon tomorrow.

55:47.831 --> 55:49.200
I take him out on the ebb.

55:49.932 --> 55:51.201
When water's high, I'll do it.

55:51.934 --> 55:53.034
Then the current will take away

55:53.036 --> 55:54.871
what the sharks leave behind.

56:06.615 --> 56:09.552
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

56:23.567 --> 56:26.369
Your mother says you can
hear me when I talk to you.

56:26.969 --> 56:28.138
How can that be, huh?

56:28.706 --> 56:30.472
That makes no sense.

56:30.474 --> 56:34.876
She never knows whether
opportunity's all around her

56:34.878 --> 56:37.481
or it pours off her like rain.

56:38.782 --> 56:42.450
I'm gonna do this, just
you and me, tomorrow.

56:42.452 --> 56:43.454
Yeah.

56:45.789 --> 56:47.988
Then maybe you can open
the goddamn curtain

56:47.990 --> 56:49.159
and step outside.

56:51.594 --> 56:54.464
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

57:01.505 --> 57:02.773
Mr. Dill.

57:03.840 --> 57:05.809
It's quite a bit
unpleasant out here.

57:08.010 --> 57:09.346
Can we go inside?

57:13.516 --> 57:16.418
My name is Reid Miller,
from Fontaine.

57:16.420 --> 57:19.019
The boat and fishing
tackle suppliers.

57:19.021 --> 57:21.789
I'm a technical representative
and head of regional sales

57:21.791 --> 57:23.860
in the latitudes that
include Plymouth.

57:24.594 --> 57:26.260
May I come in and talk to you?

57:26.262 --> 57:27.695
It's 2:30 in the morning.

57:27.697 --> 57:30.300
You're out at sea
mostly, I keep missing you.

57:31.034 --> 57:32.769
By a bigger margin every time.

57:33.603 --> 57:35.168
With the storm
keeping you ashore

57:35.170 --> 57:36.973
I thought I'd take
my opportunity.

57:39.543 --> 57:41.709
What I have in my hands
may change your life

57:41.711 --> 57:43.880
and give you the one thing
you've always wanted.

57:44.847 --> 57:46.680
Well that sounds great Reid

57:46.682 --> 57:48.451
but I've got kind of
a big day tomorrow.

57:48.885 --> 57:50.353
Yes, Mr. Dill.

57:51.054 --> 57:52.690
I know all about your big day.

57:54.157 --> 57:56.626
And I think you should
hear what I have to say.

58:14.077 --> 58:15.411
Have a seat.

58:22.418 --> 58:23.753
Can I get you something?

58:24.920 --> 58:26.489
Bigger hands.

58:26.923 --> 58:27.757
What's that?

58:28.425 --> 58:29.593
Bigger hands.

58:30.827 --> 58:33.897
Whenever I'm around fishermen
I wish I had bigger hands.

58:34.864 --> 58:35.865
I'm listening, man.

58:36.532 --> 58:37.668
What the fuck do you want?

58:38.101 --> 58:39.003
Mr. Dill.

58:39.769 --> 58:41.603
Inside this suitcase...

58:41.605 --> 58:43.204
Don't tell me you're
gonna try and sell me

58:43.206 --> 58:44.171
a fishing tackle.

58:44.173 --> 58:45.773
Yes, yes I am.

58:45.775 --> 58:47.008
At 2:30 in the morning?

58:47.010 --> 58:48.512
As I say, you're often at sea.

58:49.746 --> 58:51.382
The electrical storm
is my only opportunity.

58:52.615 --> 58:55.050
Alright listen I'm a man
who can appreciate persistence

58:55.052 --> 58:56.050
with need to fish.

58:56.052 --> 58:57.251
With me it's you.

58:57.253 --> 58:59.022
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

59:00.623 --> 59:02.759
(CHUCKLING)

59:03.126 --> 59:04.291
OK.

59:04.293 --> 59:06.394
Here's what you're
gonna do, little man.

59:06.396 --> 59:08.298
I'm gonna pour you a little nip,

59:09.065 --> 59:10.764
gonna keep the cold off of you,

59:10.766 --> 59:11.965
then you gotta get
the fuck Outta here

59:11.967 --> 59:13.702
and go back to where
you came from.

59:13.704 --> 59:15.737
I got an early start
in the morning.

59:15.739 --> 59:18.708
Actually, tomorrow you
don't sail until midday.

59:20.043 --> 59:21.642
That is to say low tide is noon

59:21.644 --> 59:23.579
and as a rule you
sail at low tide.

59:24.047 --> 59:26.649
(TENSE MUSIC)

59:29.152 --> 59:31.217
You know a lot
about me, don't you?

59:31.219 --> 59:32.422
Yes.

59:33.322 --> 59:34.490
Almost everything.

59:39.795 --> 59:40.763
(COUGHS)

59:52.675 --> 59:53.677
